'''Kim Bo-reum''' ([[Hangul]]: <U+AE40><U+BCF4><U+B984>, born 6 February 1993 in [[Daegu]]) is a female [[South Korea]]n [[speed skating|speed skater]].

Kim started [[short track speed skating]] as a child. In 2007, at the age of 14, she was selected for the South Korean national junior team and won the gold medal in the women's 2000 metre relay at the Asian Junior Short Track Speed Skating Championships.

At the end of 2010 April, however, Kim turned to long track speed skating. In January 2011, she won the silver medal in the women's 3000 meters at the [[2011 Asian Winter Games|Asian Winter Games]].

